      "description": "Offering an investment-grade 2001 BMW M3 (E46) in concours-level condition. This example features the high-revving S54B32 3.2L inline-six, utilizing six individual throttle bodies and a 8,000 RPM redline. Power is delivered via a Getrag 420G 6-speed manual gearbox to a factory M-Variable limited-slip differential. This chassis has received proactive subframe reinforcement and a comprehensive VANOS system overhaul using Beisan components. Rod bearings have been serviced to factory clearance specs. The suspension retains its original geometry with refreshed bushings and Bilstein dampers. Paint depth is consistent across all factory panels, and the interior remains immaculate with zero bolster wear on the Nappa leather. A mechanically flawless, turn-key enthusiast icon.",
